PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Ethereum Transaction Explorer
ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: What is the Ethereum Transaction Explorer?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: The Ethereum Transaction Explorer is a tool that allows you to search for and view details of recent transactions on the Ethereum blockchain in real-time.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Our app connects directly to Ethereum nodes to fetch the latest transactions as they occur. The data is processed and indexed to provide a user-friendly interface for exploring transaction details.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of information can I see?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: For each transaction, you can view the sender and recipient addresses, the amount of ETH transferred, the transaction fee, and detailed data like input data if a smart contract was executed.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Yes, the Ethereum Transaction Explorer is completely free to use. We do not charge any fees for accessing or using the data and tools provided.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about tracking new Ethereum transactions
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: This app allows you to monitor the Ethereum blockchain and receive real-time alerts whenever new transactions occur.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: We connect directly to Ethereum nodes to stream incoming transactions. You can set filters to only receive notifications for transactions you care about.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What kind of filters can I set?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: You can filter by sender address, recipient address, transaction value, and many other parameters to precisely target transactions of interest.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: How quickly will I receive notifications?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Notifications are sent out within seconds of a new transaction being mined and added to the Ethereum blockchain.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Yes, you can sign up for a 14-day free trial of our service with no commitment required. Check out our pricing plans for full details.
